    "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index acceptance threshold for CPB CFD model",
    "requirementText": "The CFD model shall be considered credible for regulatory submission if the predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) for the worst-case operating condition does not exceed RH < 10 when compared against the predicate device under equivalent flow and rotational speed conditions.",
    "rationale": "An RH threshold of less than 10 is specified to ensure the model prediction remains within acceptable bounds relative to the predicate device hemolysis performance. This threshold is consistent with the moderate model influence classification and MRL 2 requirements."
  },
